In this paper, we focus on probing LMs directly for multi-valued slot-filling task.
In a zero-shot setting, an LM is probed using prompts that include a subject and a multi-valued relation to generate a list of candidate objects. However, prior knowledge of the no. of correct objects is generally unknown. Since the LM's probabilities alone do not provide a clear indication of the objects' factual accuracy [jiang-etal-2021-know, holtzman-etal-2021-surface], we apply various selection mechanisms on the generated list to choose the correct objects.